entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: A framework for building autonomous AI agents.

entities.name: React
entities.description: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces, particularly single-page applications. It enables developers to create complex UIs from small, reusable pieces of code called components.

entities.name: PGLite
entities.description: A lightweight, embeddable, in-process SQL database engine based on SQLite.

entities.name: Node.js
entities.description: An open-source, cross-platform JavaScript runtime environment that executes JavaScript code outside of a web browser. It is typically used for back-end development.

entities.name: Anthropic
entities.description: A company focused on AI safety and research, developing large language models.

entities.name: Claude Opus 4
entities.description: An advanced large language model developed by Anthropic, known for its sophisticated reasoning and understanding capabilities.

entities.name: Claude 3.5 Sonnet
entities.description: A powerful large language model developed by Anthropic, offering a balance of performance, speed, and cost for various natural language tasks.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A voice over IP (VoIP) application and digital distribution platform designed for video gamers and content creators, allowing communication via voice calls, video calls, text messaging, and media sharing.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control using Git. It provides a distributed revision control system that emphasizes distributed development of all variants of any given project co-developed and managed by individuals.

entities.name: plugin-sql
entities.description: An ElizaOS plugin that allows for SQL database operations. It is designed to be compatible with both Node.js and browser environments.

entities.name: plugin-openai
entities.description: An ElizaOS plugin that integrates with OpenAI's API, enabling access to OpenAI models.
